course_metadata.title: Advanced Digital Technologies in Construction Project Management

content_chunks.content: Selected advanced digital technologies (Artificial Intelligence (Large Language Models), blockchain, cloud computing (collaborative platforms), Internet of Things, quantum computing) that are relevant to construction project management are introduced and their applications, opportunities and limitations are explored. The course is purely introductory in its nature and focuses on demonstrating up-to-date examples of applications that have been shown to work as well as exploring the possibilities of potential applications. Students are encouraged to interact directly with the technologies wherever possible, to explore their potential in relation to enhancing their everyday work contexts and also to think beyond current state-of-the-art to future possibilities.

Advanced digital technology for construction project management - this course delivers cutting-edge digital tools for enhanced construction site coordination and project optimization. Technology for blockchain in construction ensures secure supply chain management and smart contract implementation, while Large Language Models (LLMs) enable automated documentation and intelligent decision support systems. The course introduces cloud computing platforms for real-time collaboration and Internet of Things (IoT) integration with GPS and RFID technologies for site monitoring and asset tracking. Quantum computing applications provide advanced construction simulations and project risk analysis capabilities for complex construction scenarios. Participants gain expertise in prompt engineering for AI applications, collaborative platform utilization, and digital technology integration strategies. The curriculum prepares construction professionals to implement advanced construction management techniques, optimize project workflows through digital transformation, and leverage emerging technologies for competitive advantage in the construction industry. Students develop hands-on experience with these technologies and explore their potential to revolutionize construction project management practices.
